Vuetify v-alert.description: The v-alert component is used to convey important information to the user through the use contextual types icons and color. These default types come in in 4 variations: success, info, warning, and error. Default icons are assigned which help represent different actions each type portrays. Many parts of an alert such as border, icon, and color can also be customized to fit almost any situation.

Vuetify :active.sync.description: Holds the value of the currently active button. If the button has no value supplied, its index will be used instead. This prop supports the .sync modifier.

Vuetify :aspectRatio.description: Sets a base aspect ratio, calculated as width/height. This will only set a minimum height, the component can still grow if it has lots of content

Vuetify Calendar type.description: A string which is one of month, week, day, 4day, custom-weekly, and custom-daily. The custom types look at the start and end dates passed to the component as opposed to the value.

Vuetify active-class.description: Class bound when component is active. warning Depending upon the component, this could cause side effects. If you need to add a custom class on top of a default, just do active-class="default-class your-class"

Vuetify align-content-space-around.description: Align content to the space around.

Vuetify align-content-space-between.description: Align content to the space between.

Vuetify alt.description: Alternate text for screen readers. Leave empty for decorative images

Vuetify app.description: Designates the component as part of the application layout. Used for dynamically adjusting content sizing. Components using this prop should reside outside of v-content to function properly

Vuetify aspect-ratio.description: Calculated as width/height, so for a 1920x1080px image this will be 1.7778. Will be calculated automatically if omitted

Vuetify block.description: Expands the button to 100% of available space

Vuetify border.description: Puts a border on the element. Accepts top | right | bottom | left.

Vuetify bottom.description: Align the component towards the bottom

Vuetify card.description: Inherits border radius when used within v-card

Vuetify clipped-left.description: Designates that the applications v-navigation-drawer is clipped on the left side of the toolbar

Vuetify clipped-right.description: Designates that the applications v-navigation-drawer is clipped on the right side of the toolbar

Vuetify close-label.description: Text used for aria-label on dismissible alerts.

Vuetify color.description: Applies specified color to the control - it can be the name of material color (for example success or purple) or css color (#033 or rgba(255, 0, 0, 0.5))

Vuetify colored-border.description: Swap color from the background to the border for an alternative border look.

Vuetify cycle.description: Determines if carousel should cycle through images

Vuetify day-format.description: Formats day of the month string that appears in a day to a specified locale

Vuetify dense.description: Reduces the height of the toolbar content and extension OR Hides icon and decreases component height for a more simplistic alert.

Vuetify direction.description: Direction in which speed-dial content will show. Possible values are top, bottom, left, right.

Vuetify disabled.description: Route item is disabled or Disables the ability to open the dialog

Vuetify dismissible.description: Specifies that the Alert can be closed

Vuetify display.description: Specify to display an element as flex/inline-flex/block etc. Syntax is d-{type}. For example d-flex.

Vuetify end.description: The ending date on the calendar (inclusive) in the format of YYYY-MM-DD. This may be ignored depending on the type of the calendar.

Vuetify exact.description: Exactly match the link. Without this, '/' will match every route

Vuetify extended.description: Force the toolbar to generate the extension without using the slot

Vuetify extension-height.description: Specify an explicit height for the extended slot

Vuetify fill-height.description: Make sure that col element height is filled with parent and child. Important for Safari/Firefox if children is column element.

Vuetify first-interval.description: The first interval to display in the day view. If intervalMinutes is set to 60 and this is set to 9 the first time in the view is 9am.

Vuetify flat.description: Removes the button background color or Removes card box shadow

Vuetify gradient.description: Overlays a gradient onto the image. Only supports linear-gradient syntax, anything else should be done with classes (see examples)

Vuetify grid-list.description: Sets the gutter between grid list items ranging from 2px to 24px

Vuetify hide-delimiters.description: Hides the panel with carousel delimiters

Vuetify hide-header.description: If the header at the top of the day view should be visible.

Vuetify hide-overlay.description: Hide the display of the overlay

Vuetify hover.description: Apply a higher elevation on hover

Vuetify href.description: Will designate the component tag to <a>

Vuetify icon button.description: Designates the button as icon - round and flat

Vuetify id.description: Sets the DOM id on the component

Vuetify inset.description: Reduces the dialog content maximum width to 70%

Vuetify interval-count.description: The number of intervals to display in the day view.

Vuetify interval-format.description: Formats time of day string that appears in the interval gutter of the day and week view to specified locale

Vuetify interval-height.description: The height of an interval in pixels in the day view.

Vuetify interval-minutes.description: The number of minutes the intervals are in the day view. A common interval is 60 minutes so the intervals are an hour.

Vuetify interval-style.description: Returns CSS styling to apply to the interval.

Vuetify inverted-scroll.description: Will slide out of view when scrolling down and back into view when scrolling up

Vuetify items.description: An array of objects describing each breadcrumb. See v-breadcrumbs-item API section for all object properties. Use text property for the breadcrumb text.

Vuetify justify-space-around.description: Justify content to the space around.

Vuetify justify-space-between.description: Justify content to the space between.

Vuetify large.description: Large size button or Increase the font-size of the breadcrumb item text

Vuetify lazy.description: Conditionally renders content on mounted. Will only render content if activated

Vuetify lazy-src.description: Something to show while waiting for the main image to load, typically a small base64-encoded thumbnail. Has a slight blur filter applied. Use vuetify-loader to generate automatically

Vuetify left.description: Align the component towards the left

Vuetify mandatory.description: Forces a value to always be selected

Vuetify margin.description: The helper classes apply margin to an element ranging from 0 to 5. Each size increment was designed to align with common Material Design spacings. These classes can be applied using the following format m{direction}-{size}.

Vuetify max-days.description: The maximum number of days to display in the custom calendar if an end day is not set.

Vuetify max-height.description: Sets the maximum height for the content

Vuetify max-width.description: Sets the maximum width for the content OR sheet's container.

Vuetify min-height.description: Sets the minimum height for the content

Vuetify min-weeks.description: The minimum number of weeks to display in the month or week view.

Vuetify min-width.description: Sets the minimum width for the content

Vuetify mode.description: Sets the transition mode (does not apply to transition-group)

Vuetify month-format.description: Formats month string that appears in a day to specified locale

Vuetify multiple.description: Allows for multiple selections. Model used must be an Array

Vuetify next-icon.description: The displayed icon for forcing pagination to the next item

Vuetify now.description: Override the day & time which is considered now. This is in the format of YYYY-MM-DD hh:mm:ss. The calendar is styled according to now.

Vuetify nuxt.description: Specifies the link is a nuxt-link

Vuetify outline.description: Button or Alert will have an outline

Vuetify overflow.description: Set the overflow for an element with overflow-{axis}-hidden or simply overflow-hidden.

Vuetify overlap.description: Component will overlap the slotted content

Vuetify padding.description: The helper classes apply padding to an element ranging from 0 to 5. Each size increment was designed to align with common Material Design spacings. These classes can be applied using the following format p{direction}-{size}.

Vuetify persistent.description: Clicking outside will not dismiss the dialog

Vuetify position.description: Overrides the default to change which parts get cropped off. Uses the same syntax as background-position

Vuetify prev-icon.description: The displayed icon for forcing pagination to the previous item

Vuetify prominent.description: Displays a larger vertically centered icon to draw more attention OR Increases the height of the toolbar content and extension

Vuetify reverse.description: Sets flex direction to row or (in carousels) manually set the window to use the reverseTransition

Vuetify right.description: Align the component towards the right

Vuetify round.description: Button will be round on the sides

Vuetify scroll-off-screen.description: Will transition the toolbar and extension off screen when scrolling down

Vuetify scroll-target.description: Assign the scroll target for scroll-off-screen

Vuetify scroll-threshold.description: The amount of scroll distance down before the toolbar uses scroll-off-screen

Vuetify scroll-toolbar-off-screen.description: Will transition the toolbar off screen when scrolling down

Vuetify shaped.description: Provides an alternative active style for v-list-item.

Vuetify shift.description: Hide text of button when not active

Vuetify short-intervals.description: If true, the intervals in the day view will be 9 AM as opposed to 09:00 AM

Vuetify short-months.description: Whether the short versions of a month should be used (Jan vs January).

Vuetify short-weekdays.description: Whether the short versions of a weekday should be used (Mon vs Monday).

Vuetify show-interval-on-first.description: Checks if a given day and time should be displayed in the interval gutter of the day view.

Vuetify show-month-on-first.description: Whether the name of the month should be displayed on the first day of the month.

Vuetify size.description: Sets the height and width of the element

Vuetify sizes.description: For use with srcset, see MDN

Vuetify src.description: The image to display as a background.

Vuetify srcset.description: A set of alternate images to use based on device size.

Vuetify start.description: The starting date on the calendar (inclusive) in the format of YYYY-MM-DD. This may be ignored depending on the type of the calendar.

Vuetify tabs.description: Will set an explicit 42px height for extension. Useful when default v-tabs are used in the extended slot. If you have a custom height v-tab, you should specify a height with extensionHeight.

Vuetify tag.description: Specify a custom tag to use on the component.

Vuetify text.description: Make the background transparent and color the text.

Vuetify to.description: Will designate the component tag to <router-link>

Vuetify top.description: Align the content towards the top

Vuetify touch.description: Provide a custom left and right function when swiped left or right

Vuetify transition.description: Sets the component transition. Can be one of the built in transitions or your own.

Vuetify type.description: Specify a success, info, warning or error alert. Uses the contextual color and a pre-defined icon. Or Set the button's type attribute

Vuetify value calendar.description: A date in the format of YYYY-MM-DD which determines what span of time for the calendar.

Vuetify vertical.description: Uses a vertical transition when changing windows

Vuetify weekday-format.description: Formats day of the week string that appears in the header to specified locale

Vuetify weekdays.description: Specifies which days of the week to display. To display Monday through Friday only, a value of [1, 2, 3, 4, 5] can be used. To display a week starting on Monday a value of [1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 0] can be used.

Vuetify wrap.description: Allows children to wrap within the container if the elements use more than 100%.
